Subject: OSSTMM Security Analyst Training  Live Stream on the Web


Hi,

The OPSA professional security analyst training from ISESTORM will be
available in real time!!

This event has only been approved for 1 time. ISECOM does not directly
provide any certification training outside of the annual ISESTORM event.
ISECOM will not be offering DVDs or other recordings of this event.
This training does not include the certification exam.

Find the OPSA live on the web:

   THURSDAY APRIL 5, 2006 from 14:00 to 21:00 (GMT +1)
   FRIDAY APRIL 6, 2006 from 9:00 - 13:00 and 14:00 to 19:00 (GMT +1)

The cost is $350US for 16 hours of security analyst training in English
and all registered students will receive an electronic copy of the
ISESTORM edition of the OPSA study guide! Details on the OPSA
certification are available at www.opsa.org.

Check with your local partner to take the OPSA exam and ask about 1 and
2 day power-courses to get hands-on practice for the test.

Register for the OPSA LIVE event at:

https://www.isecom.org/opsa_streaming/

It's not just a critical knowledge transfer- it's a good cause too!
ISESTORM and certifications further improvements in ISECOM projects like
the OSSTMM and Hacker Highschool.

Sincerely,
-pete.





